@page "/"

<PageTitle>Home</PageTitle>

<h1 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Welcome to Your Financial Planning App</h1>

<p class="mb-6 text-lg text-gray-700">
    This application is designed to help you manage and analyze your personal finances. Use the navigation menu on the left to access different sections of the app. Below you'll find a brief overview of each feature and how to get started.
</p>

<ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 text-gray-800">
    <li>
        <strong>People:</strong> Add and manage individuals relevant to your financial planning, such as family members or dependents.
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Investments:</strong> Track your investment accounts, holdings, and performance over time.
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Incomes:</strong> Record sources of income, including salary, business, and passive income streams.
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Expenses:</strong> Log recurring and one-time expenses to monitor your spending habits.
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Assets:</strong> Manage your assets, such as property, vehicles, and other valuables.
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Tax Brackets:</strong> View and configure tax bracket information to assist with tax planning.
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Rollovers:</strong> Track financial rollovers, such as retirement account transfers.
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Surplus Allocations:</strong> Allocate surplus funds to savings, investments, or other goals.
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Scenarios:</strong> Create and compare financial scenarios to plan for future events or changes.
    </li>
</ul>

<div class="mt-8 p-4 bg-gray-100 rounded">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-2">Getting Started</h2>
    <ol class="list-decimal pl-6 space-y-1 text-gray-700">
        <li>Begin by adding your personal information in the <strong>People</strong> section.</li>
        <li>Enter your income sources and regular expenses to build your financial profile.</li>
        <li>Add your assets and investments for a complete overview.</li>
        <li>Use the <strong>Scenarios</strong> feature to simulate changes and plan ahead.</li>
        <li>Review your tax brackets and surplus allocations to optimize your finances.</li>
    </ol>
    <p class="mt-4 text-gray-600">
        Navigate using the menu on the left. For best results, keep your data up to date and explore different scenarios to make informed decisions.
    </p>
</div>
